# Next.js Deployment — Vercel vs Netlify Reference

Rocket.new projects default to Netlify. This file covers both platforms and
deployment patterns that apply to either. For Netlify-specific config see `rocket-netlify.mdc`.

---

## Choosing a Platform

| | Vercel | Netlify |
|---|---|---|
| Next.js origin | Same company — first-party support | Via @netlify/plugin-nextjs |
| ISR | Native, zero config | Supported via plugin |
| Edge Middleware | Native | Native |
| Image optimization | Built-in, generous free tier | Via Netlify Image CDN |
| Background tasks | Vercel Cron (Pro) | Background Functions (15 min) |
| Function timeout | 10 s free / 60 s Pro | 10 s / 26 s (paid) |
| Supabase Branching | ✅ works | ✅ works (Rocket default) |
| Speed Insights | Built-in (no code needed) | —  |
| Analytics | Built-in Web Vitals | Add-on |
| Free tier functions | 100 K invocations/month | 125 K invocations/month |

